---
const aiD = (t) => t.replace(/\bAI\b/g, '<span class="ai-text-dark">AI</span>');
const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'What kind of businesses do you work with?',
    a: 'Service businesses and growing brands that want a single team running their marketing, website, and AI workflows -instead of stitching three agencies together. We work best with teams that can close revenue from qualified leads.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How is this different from hiring a regular marketing agency?',
    a: 'Most agencies sell channels. We build the system underneath them: site, tracking, channels, and AI automation engineered as one engine. That means fewer handoffs, faster iteration, and metrics that tie back to revenue.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What does "marketing for AI" actually mean?',
    a: 'Prospects increasingly ask ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Gemini before they ever touch Google. We use Generative Engine Optimization to make sure those AI models surface and recommend your business when buyers research their options.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How long until I see results?',
    a: 'Conversion improvements on a new site show up immediately. Paid and local channels usually drive qualified leads within the first 30 days. Organic search and AI visibility compound over 90 to 180 days.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Do I need to replace my current website?',
    a: 'Not always. If your site is the bottleneck -slow, poorly converting, or built for a brochure rather than a funnel -we rebuild it. Otherwise we instrument what you have and focus the budget where it moves revenue.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How do AI workflows fit in?',
    a: 'We automate the manual lag between lead, follow-up, and close: routing, scoring, enrichment, response, reporting. Your team keeps doing the human work -closing, advising, building relationships -and the system handles the rest.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What does engagement look like?',
    a: 'We start with an audit, build the foundation, then run the channels and automation as an ongoing retainer. You get one team, one roadmap, and weekly visibility into what is moving the numbers.',
  },
];
---

<section id="faq" class="relative bg-black py-24 text-white md:py-32">
  <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 bg-grid-dark opacity-30 [mask-image:radial-gradient(ellipse_at_center,black_30%,transparent_75%)]"></div>
  <div class="pointer-events-none absolute -right-32 top-1/3 h-96 w-96 rounded-full bg-gold/10 blur-3xl"></div>

  <div class="container-x relative">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-gold-soft">
        <span class="h-px w-6 bg-gold-soft"></span>
        FAQ
      </span>
      <h2 class="mt-5 font-display text-4xl font-medium leading-[1.05] tracking-tight md:text-6xl">
        Questions, answered.
      </h2>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-xl text-base text-white/65 md:text-lg">
        The things prospects ask us most before they decide to work with Rumeira.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mx-auto mt-14 max-w-3xl divide-y divide-white/10 border-y border-white/10">
      {faqs.map((f) => (
        <details class="group faq-item">
          <summary class="flex cursor-pointer list-none items-start justify-between gap-6 py-6 transition-colors hover:text-gold-soft md:py-7">
            <span class="font-display text-lg font-medium leading-snug md:text-xl">{f.q}</span>
            <span class="mt-1 flex h-7 w-7 flex-none items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-white/15 text-gold-soft transition-all duration-300 group-open:rotate-45 group-open:border-gold-soft/60 group-open:bg-gold-soft/10" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" class="h-3 w-3">
                <path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              </svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <p class="pb-6 pr-12 text-sm leading-relaxed text-white/65 md:pb-7 md:text-base" set:html={aiD(f.a)} />
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .faq-item[open] summary { color: rgb(224 198 123 / 0.95); }
</style>
